# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if Pipfile.lock is not desired, uncomment the following line.
# lock

# poetry
#   Poetry uses pyproject.toml to manage dependencies and is check in to version control.
#   poetry.lock is also recommended to check in to version control.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   PDM stores project-wide configurations in .pdm.toml
#   and local configurations in .pdm-python.json
.pdm-python.json
.pdm.toml
#   pdm.lock is recommended to check in to version control.
# pdm.lock

